'''Gadoleic acid''' (20:1n-11) is an [[unsaturated fatty acid]]. It is a prominent component of some [[fish oil]]s including [[cod liver oil]].<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/123864/cod-liver-oil | title = Cod-liver oil | work = Encyclopædia Britannica }}</ref> It is one of a number of [[eicosenoic acid]]s.
