Sweetwater phase 1 consists of 25 GE 1.5 megawatt S turbines, Sweetwater phase 2 consists of 61 GE 1.5 megawatt SLE turbines, Sweetwater 3 consists of 90 GE 1.5 megawatt XLE turbines. Sweetwater Stage 4 was financed by Epplament Energy, Lestis Group, NextEra and Lattner Energy.
Sweetwater stage 4 employs 135 [[Mitsubishi]] 1.0 megawatt [[wind turbines]] and 46 [[Siemens Wind Power]] 2.3 megawatt turbines. Its output is being sold to San Antonio’s [[CPS Energy]] under a 20-year purchase agreement.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://interchange.puc.state.tx.us/WebApp/Interchange/Documents/34057_5_552687.PDF|title=Filing with the Texas Public Utilities Commission|last=|first=|date=|website=|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=}}</ref>
Sweetwater 5 utilizes 35 Siemens 2.3 MW turbines.
